A member of the Disciples of Sanctus Medicus, the secret sect that hid within the Xianzhou Luofu. 
With medicine, purify the heart. With elixir, transform one's body. They long to revive the ancient mysteries of Abundance, hoping to spur Xianzhou natives towards their next stage of evolution.

3024011.Introduction: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referenced entity is a paragon among the Knights of Beauty.

SkillList.Name: Piety
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Imbue Devotion
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target.

SkillList.Name: Spear & Shield
SkillList.SkillDesc: Randomly summons statues of "Speartip," "The Shield," and "The Honored."

SkillList.Name: Thus Spoke The Spirit of Love
SkillList.SkillDesc: Casts a Soul of Beauty from one of the statues. Causes the ability of the Soulfreed statue to be enhanced and to immediately take action.

SkillList.Name: Hymn of Gorgeous Courage
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to all targets.

SkillList.Name: Sin and Absolution
SkillList.SkillDesc: Casts the Souls of Beauty from all statues. Causes the ability of the Soulfreed statue to be enhanced.

SkillList.Name: Knights
SkillList.SkillDesc: Summons 4 Speartips. If statues are currently present on the field, heal their HP back to full.

SkillList.Name: Martyrdom of Grandiosity
SkillList.SkillDesc: After every use of Hymn of Gorgeous Courage, increases DMG. This effect is stackable.

3024012.Name: Argenti
3024012.Introduction:
A classic knight of the "Knights of Beauty" who is piously seeking his missing Aeon Idrila the "Beauty."
Forthright and candid, he wanders the cosmos espousing the virtues of Idrila's good name.

SkillList.Name: Piety
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Imbue Devotion
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target.

SkillList.Name: Spear & Shield
SkillList.SkillDesc: Randomly summons statues of "Speartip," "The Shield," and "The Honored."

SkillList.Name: Soul of Tenacity
SkillList.SkillDesc: Casts a Soul of Beauty from one of the statues and causes the ability of the Soulfreed statue to be enhanced.

SkillList.Name: Hymn of Gorgeous Courage
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to all targets.

SkillList.Name: Spear & Shield
SkillList.SkillDesc: Randomly summons statues of "Speartip," "The Shield," and "The Honored."

7001010.Name: Entranced Ingenium: Obedient Dracolion
7001010.Introduction:
An ingenium casually made by craftsmasters of the Artisanship Commission. It was originally an inanimate alarm bell used for warnings, but now it has been given a short-lived "life" due to certain mutations.
In battle, Obedient Dracolion can resist fatal damage.

SkillList.Name: Lion's Roar
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor DMG to a single target, with a chance to Weaken them.

SkillList.Name: Emergency Mode
SkillList.SkillDesc: Instead of being knocked down after taking fatal DMG, a certain amount of HP will be recovered and debuffs will be dispelled.

SkillList.Name: Self-Reconstruction
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Resets the number of times the Emergency Mode can be triggered.

7001011.Name: Voidranger: Reaver
7001011.Introduction: Warriors yet to perish were recast in the Warforge and gained Destruction's power. Antimatter completes their bodies, and negative particles reverberate throughout their forms.

SkillList.Name: Hunting Blade
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Vortex Leap
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target and any adjacent targets, and regenerates all Energy if the Skill destroys the target.

7001012.Name: Voidranger: Eliminator
7001012.Introduction:
Bodies that continued to be corroded by the Fragmentum after death. While their vital signs have changed, they continue to carry out their orders to eliminate.
Voidranger: Eliminators can quickly unleash multiple attacks in combat, but if they are unable to eliminate their foes, they will suffer a massive amount of damage.

SkillList.Name: Void Cannon
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Antimatter Speed Boost
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Greatly increases this unit's SPD.

SkillList.Name: Antimatter Bombardment
SkillList.SkillDesc: After attacking, gains a stack of Overheat. When Overheat reaches <unbreak>#1[i]</unbreak> stack(s), consumes a massive amount of this unit's own HP and removes Overheat. Defeating a target will also remove Overheat.

7001013.Name: Commerce Trotter
7001013.Introduction:
An interdimensional creature lost in the stars. Docile in nature. Sweet in taste. Inedible. Spends most of its life feeding and fleeing. Travelers who encounter these creatures see them as good omens.
The Commerce Trotter can provide Performance Points for other IPC Workers.

SkillList.Name: Motivation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Provides 1 Performance Point to a friendly unit aside from oneself.

SkillList.Name: Entreprenuerial Spirit
SkillList.SkillDesc: Every time the unit is attacked, the SPD of a friendly unit aside from oneself increases.

7002010.Name: Abundance Sprite: Wooden Lupus
7002010.Introduction:
Wolves draped in haze, their movement elusive and unexpected.
When the Ambrosial Arbor still stood, the Xianzhou people bred many fantastic creatures with esoteric techniques. Wooden Lupuses were one of the war beasts that walked alongside the army.

SkillList.Name: Wolf Predation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target, with a high chance to Shock the target.

SkillList.Name: Wolf Consumption
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target. If the target is in a DoT state, then all DoT effects currently applied to the target will cause DMG for 1 time. Afterward, there is a high chance to Shock the target.

SkillList.Name: Rallying Howl
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Summons 1 Shadow Jackhyena with the same Current HP as oneself.

7002011.Name: Shadow Jackhyena
7002011.Introduction: Illusion formed by a Wooden Lupus.

SkillList.Name: Wolf Predation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target, with a high chance to Shock the target.

7002020.Name: Vagrant
7002020.Introduction: In order to survive, some Underworlders are desperate enough to venture deep into the Fragmentum in search of anything salvageable. Ancient machinery that they dug up has become their best helper.

SkillList.Name: Shovel Attack
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Great Inspiration
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Increases ATK and SPD for a single chosen unit. If not chosen, then this unit immediately takes action. When battle starts, this ability starts fully Charged.

7002030.Name: Incineration Shadewalker
7002030.Introduction:
Shades that wander in the Fragmentum after the arrival of the Eternal Freeze. It mimics the form of the Silvermane Guards in a twisted manner. Fitted with the same uniformed armor as the Belobog warriors, its skull is, however, replaced by faceless embers.
Incineration Shadewalkers will swing their fiery ax and burn their enemies in battle.

SkillList.Name: Scorching Crush
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target, with a high chance to Burn the target.

SkillList.Name: Scorching Blast
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Deals massive DMG to target, and has a high chance of inflicting burn on target.

7002050.Name: Entranced Ingenium: Illumination Dragonfish
7002050.Introduction: An ingenium casually made by craftsmasters of the Artisanship Commission. It was originally an inanimate illuminator used for casting light upon darkness, but now it has been given a short-lived "life" due to certain mutations.

SkillList.Name: Nightly Luminosity
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor DMG to all targets and has a high chance to inflict a random DoT.

SkillList.Name: Display Fireworks
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Fires out spectacular fireworks that don't really do anything, but hey, they're nice to look at.

SkillList.Name: Candle Flame
SkillList.SkillDesc: When downed, deals DMG to all friendly units, with a high chance to increase their DMG received.

7002060.Name: Silvermane Cannoneer
7002060.Introduction:
A cannoneer of the Silvermane Guards who wields a portable hand cannon into battle.
During combat, a Silvermane Cannoneer will launch brutal chain attacks along with other allies of theirs.

SkillList.Name: Barrage
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target and any adjacent targets.

SkillList.Name: Lock and Load
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Provides Support to a friendly unit and increases the ATK of this unit and the Supported unit.

SkillList.Name: Covering Support
SkillList.SkillDesc: When entering battle, provides support to a friendly unit. After the supported unit attacks a target, this unit performs 1 follow-up attack, dealing minor DMG to the attacked target and adjacent targets.

7002070.Name: Imaginary Weaver
7002070.Introduction: Strange beings that do not belong to this world. Passing through countless barriers, they arrive from the other side of the vast, dark, starry sky. Their bodies are like diseased branches breaching into reality, using Imaginary power to twist reality at will.

SkillList.Name: Reverberating Carol
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target and adjacent targets. When used for the first time, this will greatly advance this unit's action.

SkillList.Name: Carolburst
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Deals massive DMG to a single target.

7002080.Name: Silvermane Gunner
7002080.Introduction:
A gunner of Belobog's Silvermane Guards, tasked with sniping at enemies.
Silvermane Gunners can mark enemy targets in combat and direct allies to focus their attacks.

SkillList.Name: Cannon Strike
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor DMG to a single target. This unit's action will be advanced by a certain percentage after this skill is used.

SkillList.Name: Piercing Grenade
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Deals DMG to a single target, causing them to take extra DMG each time they are attacked and to become the target of all units' attacks. When battle starts, this ability starts fully Charged.

7002090.Name: Silvermane Soldier
7002090.Introduction:
A member of Belobog's Silvermane Guards, tasked with leading the charge into enemy lines.
Silvermane Soldiers provide continuous buffs to allies in combat.

SkillList.Name: Tireless Charge
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Morale Booster
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. All enemies gain 5 stacks of Morale.

SkillList.Name: Silvermane Armor
SkillList.SkillDesc: After attacking a target, all friendly units (including this unit) gain a stack of Morale. Each stack of Morale increases DMG dealt and SPD while decreasing DMG taken.

7002100.Name: Automaton Spider
7002100.Introduction: An automaton pieced together with Old World technology, tasked with replacing humans in performing the most basic forms of physical labor.

SkillList.Name: Ram
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Timed Module
SkillList.SkillDesc: The next action uses Self-Exploding Module.

SkillList.Name: Self-Exploding Module
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Self-destructs, dealing DMG to a single target and adjacent targets.

7002110.Name: Automaton Spider
7002110.Introduction: An automaton pieced together with Old World technology, tasked with replacing humans in performing the most basic forms of physical labor.

SkillList.Name: Ram
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Timed Module
SkillList.SkillDesc: The next action uses Self-Exploding Module.

SkillList.Name: Self-Exploding Module
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Self-destructs, dealing DMG to a single target and adjacent targets.

7002120.Name: Grunt: Field Personnel
7002120.Introduction: An Interastral Peace Corporation grunt worker whose job mainly deals with shady "business oversights." With a meager salary, the only lodging they can afford is a shared room on one of the IPC's enterprise ships.

SkillList.Name: Clock In
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target and gains 1 Performance Point.

SkillList.Name: Annual Accounting
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all charges. Deals DMG to a single target. If they are present, Performance Points will increase DMG. All Performance Points will be expended.

SkillList.Name: IPC Employee
SkillList.SkillDesc: Greatly increases DMG in accordance with the number of Performance Points. A stackable Shield will be obtained when receiving Performance Points, and the Shield will be removed when there are no Performance Points. When the Shield is broken or the character is downed, the Performance Points will be seized.

7002130.Name: Grunt: Security Personnel
7002130.Introduction: An Interastral Peace Corporation grunt worker whose job mainly involves maintaining order in locations ruled by the IPC. With a meager salary, the only lodging they can afford is a shared room on one of the IPC's enterprise ships.

SkillList.Name: Appeal
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target and adjacent targets. Gains 1 Performance Point.

SkillList.Name: Performance Review
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Deals DMG to a single target and adjacent targets. If they are present, Performance Points will advance this unit's action by a certain proportion. All Performance Points will be expended.

SkillList.Name: IPC Employee
SkillList.SkillDesc: Greatly increases DMG in accordance with the number of Performance Points. A stackable Shield will be obtained when receiving Performance Points, and the Shield will be removed when there are no Performance Points. When the Shield is broken or the character is downed, the Performance Points will be seized.

7002140.Name: Everwinter Shadewalker
7002140.Introduction:
Shades that wander in the Fragmentum after the arrival of the Eternal Freeze. It mimics the form of the Silvermane Guards in a twisted manner. Fitted with the same uniformed armor as the Belobog warriors, its face, however, is replaced by a sheet of faceless ice.
Everwinter Shadewalkers will swing their ice axe and slow their enemies.

SkillList.Name: Frost Crush
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target and delays their action.

SkillList.Name: Frost Supercrush
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Deals DMG to a single target, with a high chance of Freezing the target.

7003010.Name: Blaze Out of Space
7003010.Introduction:
Born of the Fragmentum and created by the Stellaron, this alien life form feeds on this world's energy. The blazing fires from the core of a star burn on its armor.
In combat, the Blaze Out of Space will incinerate anything it touches.

SkillList.Name: Bellowing Inferno
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor DMG to a single target and has a high chance to inflict Enkindle.

SkillList.Name: Rain of Purifying Flames
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals successive minor DMG to a random single target, with a high chance to inflict Enkindle.

SkillList.Name: Molten Fusion
SkillList.SkillDesc: Increases this unit's ATK.

SkillList.Name: Bomb Warning
SkillList.SkillDesc: Starts charging, and unleashes Bomb en Masse for the next action.

SkillList.Name: Bomb en Masse
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Deals massive DMG to all targets.

7003020.Name: Aurumaton Gatekeeper
7003020.Introduction:
Garrison aurumaton created with ancient ingenium technology.
Countless years ago, the aurumatons set sail with the Xianzhou to seek divine recipes of immortality, and were tasked with overseeing humanity and aiding humankind during warfare. However, after countless rebellions, they were finally overpowered by the Xianzhou natives.
Now, all aurumatons are strictly controlled with talismans and are employed to guard important places.

SkillList.Name: Farewell Etiquette
SkillList.SkillDesc: The Sanction Rate level increases when your team uses Skills or Ultimates. When the Sanction Rate reaches its level cap, unleashes Sanction Mode.

SkillList.Name: Dread
SkillList.SkillDesc: Increases Sanction Rate level and deals minor DMG to all targets. Has a high chance to inflict Weaken on the targets.

SkillList.Name: Restraint
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Enchainment
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive DMG to a single target, with a high chance of inflicting Imprisonment.

SkillList.Name: Sanction Mode
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Increases SPD and when taking action, uses a powerful attack ability, lasting for 2 turns. Summons the Illumination Dragonfish at the same time.

7003030.Name: Silvermane Lieutenant
7003030.Introduction:
The leader of a squad of Belobog's Silvermane Guards.
Silvermane Lieutenants can provide Shields for allies and counterattack enemies attacking their protected allies.

SkillList.Name: Assault
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals single target DMG.

SkillList.Name: Defense Line
SkillList.SkillDesc: Applies Shields to all enemies.

SkillList.Name: Total Preparation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Has a high chance of Taunting all targets and providing massive Shields for oneself.

SkillList.Name: Silvermane Command
SkillList.SkillDesc: Automatically Counters when Shielded target is attacked.

7003040.Name: Voidranger: Trampler
7003040.Introduction:
A product of the Antimatter Legion utilizing the Warforge to recast and fuse remnants of fallen warriors and Leviathans.
Though relatively rare, they possess both the intelligence of a warrior and the power and mobility of a Leviathan. In combat, it can immediately take another action after destroying an enemy.

SkillList.Name: Unreal Projection
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Rule of Force
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: War Trample
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Deals DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target.

SkillList.Name: Spiral Arrow
SkillList.SkillDesc: Locks on to a single target. Cast "End of Bow" to this target in the next action.

SkillList.Name: End of Bow
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Anti-Matter Oppression
SkillList.SkillDesc: Gains an immediate action when target is defeated.

7003060.Name: Frigid Prowler
7003060.Introduction:
A machine unit prowling in the Fragmentum. Undoubtedly, this monstrosity is not a human creation, but one that was born out of the perversion of the Fragmentum.
Frigid Prowler will drain HP from allies to greatly enhance itself.

SkillList.Name: Ice Wheel Crusher
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Frozen Storm
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Deals DMG to all targets, with a high chance to Deep Freeze the targets.

SkillList.Name: Cryo-Extraction
SkillList.SkillDesc: When friendly units exist, consumes adjacent friendly units' HP to increase ATK and immediately take another action.

7003070.Name: Automaton Direwolf
7003070.Introduction:
An automaton pieced together with Old World technology. This rare type of humanoid automaton is equipped with a chainsaw on its right arm, presumably used for mining or construction operations.
In combat, Automaton Direwolfs can continuously stack SPD and DMG buffs.

SkillList.Name: Felling Order
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG, with each hit having a low chance to inflict Bleed.

SkillList.Name: Combat Speed-Up
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Gains 3 stacks of Pressure, with each stack increasing ATK and SPD.

SkillList.Name: Lock On Target
SkillList.SkillDesc: When the battle begins or when the locked on target is downed, locks on to a single target and gains 3 stacks of Pressure.

SkillList.Name: Dismantle
SkillList.SkillDesc: After using Felling Order, there is a chance to deliver a follow-up attack and get 1 stack of Pressure. The more HP the target has already lost, the higher the chances of delivering a follow-up attack.

7003080.Name: Searing Prowler
7003080.Introduction:
A machine unit prowling in the Fragmentum. Undoubtedly, this monstrosity is not a human creation, but one that was born out of the perversion of the Fragmentum.
Searing Prowler's attacks will deal extra damage against enemies afflicted with Burn.

SkillList.Name: Crimson Blade
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target, with a high chance to Burn the target.

SkillList.Name: Combustion Slash
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target and any adjacent targets.

SkillList.Name: Melt
SkillList.SkillDesc: After attacking a Burned target, receives a DMG increase.

SkillList.Name: High-Temperature Operation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Slightly increases ATK and greatly increases SPD.

SkillList.Name: Dancing Cinders
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to all targets. Targets suffering from Burn are dealt additional DMG and have Burn removed.

SkillList.Name: Scorching Burst
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Deals DMG to all targets. Burned target will explode, subsequently dealing DMG to the Burned target and units adjacent to the target. The Burn status will be removed afterward.

SkillList.Name: Augury of Fireburst
SkillList.SkillDesc: Uses Scorching Burst in the next action.

7003090.Name: Automaton Grizzly
7003090.Introduction:
An automaton pieced together with Old World technology. It's been reinforced with durable armor to charge forward and protect the Silvermane Guards.
In combat, an Automaton Grizzly will summon Automaton Spiders and unleash a powerful charged attack.

SkillList.Name: Detonation Order
SkillList.SkillDesc: Summons Automaton Spider.

SkillList.Name: Enrage Order
SkillList.SkillDesc: Has a chance to Taunt all targets.

SkillList.Name: Overcombust Order
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Charge state. The next action uses Purge Order on all targets.

SkillList.Name: Purge Order
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive DMG to all targets.

SkillList.Name: Destruction Order
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target.

7003100.Name: Senior Staff: Team Leader
7003100.Introduction: An Interastral Peace Corporation senior staff member with a minimal rank of project team leader. The mech they drive belongs to the IPC. If damaged, its repair fees have to be paid out-of-pocket. With a half-decent salary, they can at least afford to rent a one-bedroom apartment on one of the IPC's enterprise ships.

SkillList.Name: Disciplined
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals DMG to a single target, and if there are no Performance Points at the time, gains 1 Performance Point. Otherwise, consumes all Performance Points.

SkillList.Name: Cost Reduction
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive DMG to a single target and gains 1 Performance Point.

SkillList.Name: In Training...
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Charge state. Uses Work Culture Shock for the next action.

SkillList.Name: Work Culture Shock
SkillList.SkillDesc: Consumes all Charges. Deals massive DMG to all targets and expends all Performance Points.

SkillList.Name: <unbreak>720</unbreak>-Degree Review
SkillList.SkillDesc: Seizes 1 Performance Points from all other friendly units.

SkillList.Name: Team Building
SkillList.SkillDesc: Summons Interastral Peace Corporation Employee and gains 1 Performance Point.

SkillList.Name: IPC Employee
SkillList.SkillDesc: Greatly increases DMG in accordance with the number of Performance Points. A stackable Shield will be obtained when receiving Performance Points, and the Shield will be removed when there are no Performance Points. When the Shield is broken or the character is downed, the Performance Points will be seized.

8001010.Name: Flamespawn
8001010.Introduction: Crystallized elements with only the simplest intelligence. It drifts in the Fragmentum in the form of a bird emitting intense heat, burning everything in its path.

SkillList.Name: Distract
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Fire DMG to a single target.

8001020.Name: Frostspawn
8001020.Introduction: Crystallized elements with only the simplest intelligence. It drifts in the Fragmentum in the form of a bird releasing eerily low temperatures, freezing everything around it.

SkillList.Name: Distract
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Ice DMG to a single target.

8001030.Name: Mask of No Thought
8001030.Introduction: Victims of Fragmentum corrosion pieced together into one bizarre creature, their numb faces forming a sphere without thought or emotion. Any part that was once human has since vanished.

SkillList.Name: Iridescent Beam
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Imaginary DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Focused Charge
SkillList.SkillDesc: Increases the ATK of all friendly units.

SkillList.Name: Energy Burst
SkillList.SkillDesc: All targets' Energy gets regenerated after this unit suffers a killing blow.

8001040.Name: Thunderspawn
8001040.Introduction: Crystallized elements with only the simplest intelligence. It drifts in the Fragmentum in the form of a bird brimming with electricity, releasing thunderclaps in all directions.

SkillList.Name: Thunderflash
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Lightning DMG to a single target, with a high chance to Shock the target.

8001050.Name: Windspawn
8001050.Introduction: Crystallized elements with only the simplest intelligence. It drifts in the Fragmentum in the form of a bird engulfed in twisting winds, raging on like a tornado.

SkillList.Name: Windpath
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Wind DMG to a single target, with a high chance to inflict Wind Shear.

8002010.Name: Imaginary Weaver
8002010.Introduction: Strange beings that do not belong to this world. Passing through countless barriers, they arrive from the other side of the vast, dark, starry sky. Their bodies are like diseased branches breaching into reality, using Imaginary power to twist reality at will.

SkillList.Name: Carolbeam
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Imaginary DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Carolburst
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive Imaginary DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Reverberating Carol
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Imaginary DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target, and enters a Defensive Position. In the next turn, use Carolburst and massively increase the DMG dealt.

SkillList.Name: Imaginary Armor
SkillList.SkillDesc: Receives reduced DMG from non-Weakness Type attacks.

8002040.Name: Warp Trotter
8002040.Introduction: An interdimensional creature lost in the stars. Docile in nature. Sweet in taste. Inedible. Spends most of its life feeding and fleeing. Travelers who encounter these creatures see them as good omens.

SkillList.Name: SSSScared
SkillList.SkillDesc: The Treasure Trotter got spooked and will flee in 2 turns.

SkillList.Name: Run... Run!
SkillList.SkillDesc: The Treasure Trotter is panicking and will flee in 1 turn.

SkillList.Name: Phew... Escaped
SkillList.SkillDesc: The Trotter flees in an instant.

8002050.Name: Sequence Trotter

SkillList.SkillDesc: The Treasure Trotter is panicking and will flee in 1 turn.

SkillList.Name: Phew... Escaped
SkillList.SkillDesc: The Trotter flees in an instant.

8002052.Name: Trot Deuce
8002052.Introduction: An interdimensional creature lost in the stars. Docile in nature. Sweet in taste. Inedible. Spends most of its life feeding and fleeing. Travelers who encounter these creatures see them as good omens.

SkillList.Name: SSSScared
SkillList.SkillDesc: The Treasure Trotter got spooked and will flee in 2 turns.

SkillList.Name: Run... Run!
SkillList.SkillDesc: The Treasure Trotter is panicking and will flee in 1 turn.

SkillList.Name: Phew... Escaped

8003010.Name: Ice Out of Space
8003010.Introduction:
A strange being that does not belong to this world. Nurtured in the Fragmentum brought by the Stellaron, it feeds upon this world's root structures to obtain energy. Its armor reflects the gloomy and profound starry sky.
In combat, the Ice Out of Space will freeze targets it touches.

Baryons have basic intelligence, and can clear the path according to the commands and summons of Voidrangers on the battlefield.

SkillList.Name: Obliterate
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Quantum DMG to a single target.

8011020.Name: Antibaryon

8012010.Name: Voidranger: Reaver
8012010.Introduction:
Warriors yet to perish were recast in the Warforge and gained Destruction's power. Antimatter completes their bodies and negative particles reverberate throughout their forms.
Violently aggressive, they embody the will of Destruction and are basic combat units of the Antimatter Legion, acting only according to their destructive instincts.

SkillList.Name: Hunting Blade
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Imaginary DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Vortex Leap
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Imaginary DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target.

8012020.Name: Voidranger: Distorter
8012020.Introduction:
A Voidranger that has successfully survived particle annihilation, the positive and negative particles in its body have temporarily achieved a strange balance, granting them more power than ordinary reavers.
Basic combat units of the Antimatter Legion. They possess some intelligence and are able to control reavers within a small surrounding area.

SkillList.Name: Nihility's Command
SkillList.SkillDesc: Locks Onto a random unit on your team, making them the target for incoming attacks from all of their enemies.

SkillList.Name: Shadowless Void Strike
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Quantum DMG to a single target.

8012030.Name: Voidranger: Eliminator

8015010.Name: Doomsday Beast
8015010.Introduction: Using fragments of the Dusk Leviathan as the foundation, and the weeping bones of thousands of the dead in the Warforge as the agent, the Antimatter Legion cast the Doomsday Beast. The resentful spirits' senseless obsession turns into a tangible hand, and the shadow of the old disaster conceals the heavens. The Doomsday Beast detains the will of all beings that are not at ease and have yet to die. Anger, mourning, or delusional joy  all is revealed, and all evil eagerly throb. The Doomsday Beast's core is a dark matter engine.

SkillList.Name: Leviathan's Lingering Power
SkillList.SkillDesc: The Doomsday Beast cannot be attacked until the Antimatter Engine, Disaster's Right Hand, and Dawn's Left Hand have all been destroyed.

SkillList.Name: Transmission Pheromone
SkillList.SkillDesc: For every True Stings spawned on the field, all True Stings gain 1 stack of DMG Boost. Only 1 Transmission Pheromone can take effect in battle at a time.

SkillList.Name: Entomon Eulogy
SkillList.SkillDesc: When receiving a killing blow, deals Wind DMG to all friendly units, with a high chance to slightly increase their DMG received.

SkillList.Name: Propagation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Spawns True Stings.

8024012.Name: Swarm: True Sting (Complete)
8024012.Introduction: A complete projection produced by compromised codes. The referenced entity is a mature True Sting. Sir Duroy, a member of the Intelligentsia Guild, explored the starry seas and authored the thirty-volume of the Chronicles of Interdimensional Insects. The book provides detailed records of over a dozen confirmed species of lepisma and countless subspecies spanning across the stars.

SkillList.Name: Time to Battle
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Wind DMG to a single target, with a high chance to inflict 2 stacks of Wind Shear.

SkillList.Name: War Gear
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Wind DMG to a single target. If the target is currently suffering from Wind Shear, Wind Shear immediately causes DMG 1 time.

SkillList.Name: Cyclonic Swarm
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Wind DMG to all targets, with a high chance to cause Wind Shear.

SkillList.Name: Propagation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Spawns True Stings.

SkillList.Name: Ready Order
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Charge state. Uses Swarm Onslaught for the next action.

8025010.Name: Starcrusher Swarm King: Skaracabaz (Synthetic)
8025010.Introduction: The replica of the Emanator of Propagation cultivated by Ruan Mei, briefly manifesting in the world in an incomplete form. Its original form is a giant lepisma that inherited the mandibles of the Imperator Insectorum. It can collect in its mouthparts the death ray that fragmented celestial bodies, and make shattered stars incubators for procreating offspring. It was once one of the nightmares across multiple worlds during the Swarm Disaster.

SkillList.Name: Swarm King Cannon
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Quantum DMG to a single target

SkillList.Name: Radiating Venom
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Quantum DMG to a single target, with a high chance to inflict Entanglement. Also summons 1 Gnaw Sting.

SkillList.Name: Pyrolysis Death Beam
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Quantum DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target.

SkillList.Name: Carapace of Begotten Spawn
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enter the Multiply state until the next action. During this time, DMG received is greatly reduced, and each attack taken will cause a Gnaw Sting to be summoned. If this unit is Weakness Broken while in the Multiply state, it will deal Toughness-Reducing DMG equal to this unit's Max Toughness to all friendly units and increase the DMG taken by all other friendly units besides the target themselves.

SkillList.Name: Ovum of Collapsed Star
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive Quantum DMG to all targets.

SkillList.Name: Carapace of Nurtured Disaster
SkillList.SkillDesc: Charges and enters the Multiply state until the next action, whereupon Ovum of Collapsed Star will be used on all targets. During the Multiply state, DMG received is greatly reduced, and each attack taken will cause a Gnaw Sting or Lesser Sting to be summoned. If this unit is Weakness Broken while in the Multiply state, it will deal Toughness-Reducing DMG equal to this unit's Max Toughness to all friendly units and increase the DMG taken by all other friendly units besides the target themselves.

8032010.Name: Grunt: Field Personnel
8032010.Introduction: An Interastral Peace Corporation grunt worker whose job mainly deals with shady "business oversights." With a meager salary, the only lodging they can afford is a shared room on one of the IPC's enterprise ships.

SkillList.Name: Clock In
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Physical DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Performance Boost
SkillList.SkillDesc: Receives 1 Performance Point after unleashing an attack. Performance Points can be seized by the attacker when this unit's Weakness is Broken or this unit receives a killing blow.

8032020.Name: Grunt: Security Personnel
8032020.Introduction: An Interastral Peace Corporation grunt worker whose job mainly involves maintaining order in locations ruled by the IPC. With a meager salary, the only lodging they can afford is a shared room on one of the IPC's enterprise ships.

Silvermane Lieutenants can raise a giant shield during combat and Enhance themselves. Attacking a Silvermane Lieutenant with their shield raised will immediately result in a fierce Counter.

SkillList.Name: Assault
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Pierce
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive Physical DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Shield Reflect
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Counter state. When attacked by a single character, acts immediately and casts "Pierce" on the attacker.

SkillList.Name: Reinforcement
SkillList.SkillDesc: Summons Silvermane Soldiers or Silvermane Gunners

100401001.Name: Cocolia
100401001.Introduction:
The Guardian of Belobog, and the indisputable ruler of the Towering Citadel, Belobog.
Cocolia possesses the divine authority passed down through the generations of Guardians, giving her command over ice and snow to freeze her enemies in battle.

SkillList.Name: Chill of Bone-Piercing Coagulation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Ice DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Omen of Everlasting Freeze
SkillList.SkillDesc: Summons Ice Edges.

SkillList.Name: Punishment of Endless Winter
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive Ice DMG to all targets.

SkillList.Name: Hoarfrost of Eternal Isolation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Ice DMG to a single target, with a high chance to Freeze the target.

SkillList.Name: Wrath of Winterland Saints
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Charge state. The next action casts "Punishment of Endless Winter" on all targets.

100401002.Name: Cocolia
100401002.Introduction:
The Guardian of Belobog, and the indisputable ruler of the Towering Citadel, Belobog.
Cocolia possesses the divine authority passed down through the generations of Guardians, giving her command over ice and snow to freeze her enemies in battle.

SkillList.Name: Chill of Bone-Piercing Coagulation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Ice DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Omen of Everlasting Freeze
SkillList.SkillDesc: Summons Ice Edges.

SkillList.Name: Punishment of Endless Winter
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive Ice DMG to all targets.

SkillList.Name: Hoarfrost of Eternal Isolation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Ice DMG to a single target, with a high chance to Freeze the target.

SkillList.Name: Wrath of Winterland Saints
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Charge state. The next action casts "Punishment of Endless Winter" on all targets.

100402001.Name: Gepard
100402001.Introduction:
Captain of the Silvermane Guards.
Gepard can command his soldiers to focus their attacks, and provide each of them with a barrier that blocks one attack.

SkillList.Name: Fist of Conviction
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Ice DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Smite of Frost
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Ice DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Garrison Aura Field
SkillList.SkillDesc: Grants a Barrier to another friendly unit. The Barrier nullifies all DMG received except for DoT until after the friendly unit is attacked.

SkillList.Name: Frigid Waterfall
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Ice DMG to all targets.

SkillList.Name: Siege Support
SkillList.SkillDesc: Summons Silvermane Gunners or Silvermane Cannoneers and Locks Onto a single target for all attacks.

Bronya can use various tactics to attack her enemies, and greatly enhance the battle prowess of all allies.

101202001.Introduction:
An automaton pieced together with Old World technology, tasked with replacing humans in performing the most basic forms of physical labor.
In combat, Automaton Spiders are highly unstable, capable of exploding when damaged.

SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Physical DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Timed Module
SkillList.SkillDesc: The next action uses Self-Exploding Module.

SkillList.Name: Self-Exploding Module
SkillList.SkillDesc: Self-destructs, dealing Fire DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target.

SkillList.Name: Chains of Destruction
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Fire DMG to adjacent units when suffering a killing blow.

101401001.Name: Svarog
101401001.Introduction:
This ancient relic from the Old World was an automated control unit left behind during the times of the Geomarrow Development Group. Unlike other mindless machines that could only receive instructions, Svarog is capable of complex thoughts.
In battle, Svarog summons mechanical arms to grab and control his enemies, delivering devastating attacks.

SkillList.Name: Banishing Punch
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Burning Beam
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to a single target and delays their action.

SkillList.Name: Oppressive Embrace
SkillList.SkillDesc: Restrains a single target, preventing them from taking action or being targeted. The Restraint is dispelled if the Auxiliary Robot Arm Unit suffers Weakness Break.

SkillList.Name: Shrewd Bombing
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive Physical DMG to all targets, with a high chance to reduce their DEF.

SkillList.Name: Controlled Blasting
SkillList.SkillDesc: The Auxiliary Robot Arm Unit explodes, dealing massive Physical DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Overload Warning
SkillList.SkillDesc: Auxiliary Robot Arm Unit enters Overload Countdown, causing the next action to cast Controlled Blasting.

SkillList.Name: Boost Deployment
SkillList.SkillDesc: Summons Auxiliary Robot Arm Unit.

102201001.Name: Everwinter Shadewalker
102201001.Introduction:
Shades that wander in the Fragmentum after the arrival of the Eternal Freeze. It mimics the form of the Silvermane Guards in a twisted manner. Fitted with the same uniformed armors as the Belobog warriors, its skull is however replaced by an icicle of faceless ice.
Everwinter Shadewalkers will swing their ice ax and slow their enemies in battle.

SkillList.Name: Frost Crush
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Ice DMG to a single target and delays their action.

Shades that wander in the Fragmentum after the arrival of the Eternal Freeze. It mimics the form of the Silvermane Guards in a twisted manner. Fitted with the same uniformed armors as the Belobog warriors, its skull is however replaced by faceless embers.
Incineration Shadewalkers will swing their fiery ax and burn their enemies in battle.

SkillList.Name: Scorching Crush
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Fire DMG to a single target, with a high chance to Burn the target.

102301001.Name: Searing Prowler
102301001.Introduction:
A machine unit prowling in the Fragmentum. Undoubtedly, this monstrosity is not a human creation, but one that was born out of the perversion of the Fragmentum.
Searing Prowler's attacks will deal extra damage against enemies afflicted with Burn.

SkillList.Name: Crimson Blade
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Fire DMG to a single target, with a high chance to Burn the target.

SkillList.Name: Combustion Slash
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Fire DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target. This attack prioritizes targets afflicted with Burn.

SkillList.Name: Melt
SkillList.SkillDesc: After attacking a Burned target, receives a DMG increase.

SkillList.Name: High-Temperature Operation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Slightly increases ATK and greatly increases SPD. This buff is dispelled upon Weakness Break.

SkillList.Name: Dancing Cinders
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Fire DMG to all targets. Targets suffering from Burn are dealt an extra Fire DMG and have Burn removed.

200401001.Name: Stellaron Hunter: Kafka

201301002.Name: Aurumaton Gatekeeper
201301002.Introduction:
Garrison aurumaton created with ancient ingenium technology.
Countless years ago, the aurumatons set sail with the Xianzhou to seek divine recipes of immortality, and were tasked to oversee humanity and to aid humankind during warfare. However, after countless rebellions, they were finally overpowered by the Xianzhou natives.
Now, all aurumatons are strictly controlled with talismans, and are employed to guard important places.

201301005.Name: Aurumaton Gatekeeper
201301005.Introduction:
Garrison aurumaton created with ancient ingenium technology.
Countless years ago, the aurumatons set sail with the Xianzhou to seek divine recipes of immortality, and were tasked to oversee humanity and to aid humankind during warfare. However, after countless rebellions, they were finally overpowered by the Xianzhou natives.
Now, all aurumatons are strictly controlled with talismans, and are employed to guard important places.

201302001.Name: Aurumaton Spectral Envoy
201302001.Introduction:
A law-enforcing aurumaton engraved with the Ten-Lords Martial Scriptures and taking orders from the Ten-Lords Commission.
Living beings are susceptible to the corporeal and mental existence of the self, but gold and metal will never be swayed and will unwaveringly follow the Ten-Lords' edicts.
These aurumaton law enforcers use their strength to subdue evils that have strayed from the natural order of life, and bring them to the Netherworld to meet their sentence. Its authority is sometimes even greater than that of a judge.

SkillList.Name: Adjudicate
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Subdue
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to a single target and has a high chance to inflict Reverberation on the target. After targets afflicted with Reverberation receive an attack, they enter the Strong Reverberation state and then have the Reverberation state dispelled. Targets with Strong Reverberation cannot take action.

SkillList.Name: Revert Yin and Yang
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to all targets and has a chance to inflict Reverberation.

SkillList.Name: Heaven's Fall
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive Physical DMG to a single ally. If the target is afflicted with Strong Reverberation, they additionally take Physical DMG, and Strong Reverberation is then dispelled.

SkillList.Name: Soul Warrant
SkillList.SkillDesc: When there are targets afflicted with Strong Reverberation on the field, lock on to those targets and during the next action, use Heaven's Fall on them.

SkillList.Name: Heaven's Fall

202401001.Name: Abundant Ebon Deer
202401001.Introduction:
An auspicious spiritual beast wrought into being by the Ambrosial Arbor and protects its roots. Its arrival brings along exuberant vegetation and promises good fortune.
Once destroyed during ancient wars, the Ambrosial Arbor is mended by the Stellaron and finally revives. Rare creatures and legendary beasts made by celestials of the past all return to this world, like an old dream coming alive again.

800201001.Name: Imaginary Weaver
800201001.Introduction: Strange beings that do not belong to this world. Passing through countless barriers, they arrive from the other side of the vast, dark, starry sky. Their bodies are like diseased branches breaching into reality, using Imaginary power to twist reality at will.

SkillList.Name: Carolbeam
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Imaginary DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Carolburst
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive Imaginary DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Reverberating Carol
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Imaginary DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target, and enters a Defensive Position. In the next turn, use Carolburst and massively increase the DMG dealt.

SkillList.Name: Imaginary Armor
SkillList.SkillDesc: Receives reduced DMG from non-Weakness Type attacks.

800204001.Introduction: An interdimensional creature lost in the stars. Docile in nature. Sweet in taste. Inedible. Spends most of its life feeding and fleeing. Travelers who encounter these creatures see them as good omens.

SkillList.Name: SSSScared
SkillList.SkillDesc: The Treasure Trotter got spooked and will flee in 2 turns.

SkillList.Name: Run... Run!
SkillList.SkillDesc: The Treasure Trotter is panicking and will flee in 1 turn.

SkillList.Name: Phew... Escaped
SkillList.SkillDesc: The Trotter flees in an instant.

SkillList.Name: PProtect You
SkillList.SkillDesc: When entering battle, applies "PProtect You" to all friendly units. Each stack of "PProtect You" can nullify all DMG received from 1 incoming hit except for DoT. "PProtect You" stacks are shared across the team.

800301001.Name: Ice Out of Space
800301001.Introduction:
A strange being that does not belong to this world. Nurtured in the Fragmentum brought by the Stellaron, it feeds upon this world's root structures to obtain energy. Its armor reflects the gloomy and profound starry sky.
In combat, the Ice Out of Space will freeze targets it touches.

SkillList.Name: Chilling Lament
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Ice DMG to a single target. Deals extra Ice DMG to the target if the target is currently Frozen and this unit is in the Freezing Point state.

SkillList.Name: Frosty Absorption
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Freezing Point state. Everwinter Rain can be used in subsequent attacks.

SkillList.Name: Everwinter Rain
SkillList.SkillDesc: This ability is only available while in the Freezing Point state. Deals minor Ice DMG to all targets, with a chance to Freeze the targets.

SkillList.Name: Chilling Lament
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Ice DMG to a single target. There is a chance to Freeze the target if the user is in the Freezing Point state.

A strange being that does not belong to this world. Nurtured in the Fragmentum brought by the Stellaron, it feeds upon this world's root structures to obtain energy. Its armor reflects the gloomy and profound starry sky.
In combat, the Ice Out of Space will freeze targets it touches.

SkillList.Name: Chilling Lament
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Ice DMG to a single target. Deals extra Ice DMG to the target if the target is currently Frozen and this unit is in the Freezing Point state.

SkillList.Name: Frosty Absorption
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Freezing Point state. Everwinter Rain can be used in subsequent attacks.

SkillList.Name: Everwinter Rain
SkillList.SkillDesc: This ability is only available while in the Freezing Point state. Deals minor Ice DMG to all targets, with a chance to Freeze the targets.

SkillList.Name: Chilling Lament
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Ice DMG to a single target. There is a chance to Freeze the target if the user is in the Freezing Point state.

800302001.Name: Blaze Out of Space
800302001.Introduction:
A strange being that does not belong to this world. Nurtured in the Fragmentum created by the Stellaron, it parasitize upon this world's root structures to obtain energy. Its armor burns with the blazing flames in the core of stars.
In combat, the Blaze Out of Space will incinerate anything it touches.

SkillList.Name: Bellowing Inferno
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Fire DMG to a single target and has a high chance to inflict Enkindle.

SkillList.Name: Blazing Absorption
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Spontaneous Combustion state. Rain of Purifying Flames can be used in subsequent attacks.

SkillList.Name: Rain of Purifying Flames
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals successive minor Fire DMG to a random single target, with a high chance to inflict Enkindle.

SkillList.Name: Molten Fusion
SkillList.SkillDesc: Gains ATK. This buff is dispelled upon Weakness Break.

800303001.Name: Guardian Shadow
800303001.Introduction:
A shadow manifested by the power of a Stellaron, carrying out the Fragmentum's unceasing will to expand.
A living being of energy born from the projection of the desires of sentient lifeforms into the Fragmentum, akin to a pearl created from a single grain of sand. This energy wanders around aimlessly, acting only when executing the will of its master.

SkillList.Name: Lightning Recollection
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Lightning DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Lightning Condemnation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Lightning DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target.

SkillList.Name: Tranquil Ban
SkillList.SkillDesc: Your team is imposed with a ban on attacking the Guardian Shadow. Should anyone do so, they immediately receive 1 attack.

SkillList.Name: Disarm Ban
SkillList.SkillDesc: Your team is imposed with a ban on using Basic ATK. Should anyone do so, they immediately receive 1 attack.

SkillList.Name: Silent Ban
SkillList.SkillDesc: Your team is imposed with a ban on using Skill. Should anyone do so, they immediately receive 1 attack.

SkillList.Name: Thunderstorm Condemnation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals successive minor Lightning DMG to a random target, with a chance to inflict Shock.

SkillList.Name: Inevitable Punishment
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Lightning DMG to whoever violates the ban.

A living being of energy born from the projection of the desires of sentient lifeforms into the Fragmentum, akin to a pearl created from a single grain of sand. This energy wanders around aimlessly, acting only when executing the will of its master.

SkillList.Name: Lightning Recollection
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Lightning DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Lightning Condemnation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Lightning DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target.

SkillList.Name: Tranquil Ban
SkillList.SkillDesc: Your team is imposed with a ban on attacking the Guardian Shadow. Should anyone do so, they immediately receive 1 attack.

SkillList.Name: Disarm Ban
SkillList.SkillDesc: Your team is imposed with a ban on using Basic ATK. Should anyone do so, they immediately receive 1 attack.

SkillList.Name: Silent Ban
SkillList.SkillDesc: Your team is imposed with a ban on using Skill. Should anyone do so, they immediately receive 1 attack.

SkillList.Name: Thunderstorm Condemnation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals successive minor Lightning DMG to a random target, with a chance to inflict Shock.

SkillList.Name: Inevitable Punishment
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Lightning DMG to whoever violates the ban.

800304001.Name: Decaying Shadow
800304001.Introduction:
A shadow manifested by the power of a Stellaron, carrying out the Fragmentum's unceasing will to expand.
A living being of energy born from the projection of the desires of sentient lifeforms into the Fragmentum, akin to a pearl created from a single grain of sand. However, the desire that drove it has long since been twisted and distorted.

SkillList.Name: Fleeting Gilded Spikes
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Imaginary DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Fleeting Punishment
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive Imaginary DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Binding of the Golden Age
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Charge state and gains 9 Gauge Recollection stacks. Casts Liberation of the Golden Age in the next action. Every time this unit is attacked, lose 1 stack of Gauge Recollection.

SkillList.Name: Liberation of the Golden Age
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals successive minor Imaginary DMG to a random target. The number of attacks is equal to the "Gauge Recollection" stacks remaining. If there is no "Gauge Recollection," this ability will fail.

SkillList.Name: Fleeting Veil
SkillList.SkillDesc: Slightly reduces DMG received from Basic ATKs, Skills, Ultimates, and follow-up attacks, with a small chance to inflict Imprisonment on the target attacked by Decaying Shadow.

800305001.Name: Stormbringer
800305001.Introduction:
Monsters that have experienced corrosion as the Fragmentum expanded. They now have a more nimble way of fighting after the source of their power mutated.
Stormbringers utilize the power of the wind to aid them in battle, enabling them to fire arrows more rapidly.

SkillList.Name: Watchful Meteor
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Wind DMG to a single target and has a high chance to inflict Wind Shear.

SkillList.Name: Wind Walker
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Wind DMG to the target and units adjacent to the target, with a chance to inflict Wind Shear.

SkillList.Name: Wind-Twisting Crossbow
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Charge state and locks on to all targets currently suffering Wind Shear. Cast Windfall Storm in the next action.

SkillList.Name: Windfall Storm
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Wind DMG to targets afflicted with Wind Shear. This ability fails if no one on the target team suffers Wind Shear.

SkillList.Name: Storm Cyclone
SkillList.SkillDesc: Slightly increases ATK after attacking a target afflicted with Wind Shear. This buff is dispelled upon Weakness Break.

SkillList.Name: Windfall Storm
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Wind DMG to targets afflicted with Wind Shear. This ability fails if no one on the target team suffers Wind Shear.

801203001.Name: Voidranger: Eliminator
801203001.Introduction:

Voidranger: Eliminators will mark enemies they hit, causing them to take extra damage when attacked.

SkillList.SkillDesc: Dispels this unit's Overloaded state.

801301001.Name: Voidranger: Trampler
801301001.Introduction:
A product of the Antimatter Legion utilizing the Warforge to recast and fuse remnants of fallen warriors and Leviathans.
Though relatively rare, they possess both the intelligence of a warrior and the power and mobility of a Leviathan. Its screech can summon a large number of Voidrangers.

SkillList.Name: Unreal Projection
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Quantum DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Rule of Force
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Quantum DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: War Trample
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Quantum DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target.

SkillList.Name: Spiral Arrow
SkillList.SkillDesc: Locks on to a single target. Cast End of Bow to this target in the next action.

SkillList.Name: End of Bow
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive Quantum DMG to a single target, with a high chance to inflict Entanglement.

802202001.Name: Lesser Sting
802202001.Introduction: The youngling of a True Sting. Based on their growth stage, young True Stings can be further divided into Juvenile Stings and Lesser Stings.

SkillList.Name: Prepare to Fight
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Charge state. Uses Bursting Detonation for the next action.

SkillList.Name: Bursting Detonation
SkillList.SkillDesc: Detonates self and deals Wind DMG to a target and its adjacent targets, with a high chance to cause Outrage to the target.

SkillList.Name: Entomon Eulogy
SkillList.SkillDesc: When receiving a killing blow, deals Wind DMG to all friendly units, with a high chance to slightly increase their DMG received.

802501001.Name: Starcrusher Swarm King: Skaracabaz (Synthetic)
802501001.Introduction: The replica of the Emanator of Propagation cultivated by Ruan Mei, briefly manifesting in the world in an incomplete form. Its original form is a giant lepisma that inherited the mandibles of the Imperator Insectorum. It can collect in its mouthparts the death ray that fragmented celestial bodies, and make shattered stars incubators for procreating offspring. It was once one of the nightmares across multiple worlds during the Swarm Disaster.

SkillList.Name: Swarm King Cannon
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Quantum DMG to a single target

SkillList.Name: Radiating Venom
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Quantum DMG to a single target, with a high chance to inflict Entanglement. Also summons 1 Gnaw Sting.

SkillList.Name: Pyrolysis Death Beam
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Quantum DMG to a single target and units adjacent to the target.

SkillList.Name: Carapace of Begotten Spawn
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enter the Multiply state until the next action. During this time, DMG received is greatly reduced, and each attack taken will cause a Gnaw Sting to be summoned. If this unit is Weakness Broken while in the Multiply state, it will deal Toughness-Reducing DMG equal to this unit's Max Toughness to all friendly units and increase the DMG taken by all other friendly units besides the target themselves.

SkillList.Name: Ovum of Collapsed Star
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals massive Quantum DMG to all targets.

SkillList.Name: Carapace of Nurtured Disaster
SkillList.SkillDesc: Charges and enters the Multiply state until the next action, whereupon Ovum of Collapsed Star will be used on all targets. During the Multiply state, DMG received is greatly reduced, and each attack taken will cause a Gnaw Sting or Lesser Sting to be summoned. If this unit is Weakness Broken while in the Multiply state, it will deal Toughness-Reducing DMG equal to this unit's Max Toughness to all friendly units and increase the DMG taken by all other friendly units besides the target themselves.

803201001.Name: Grunt: Field Personnel
803201001.Introduction: An Interastral Peace Corporation grunt worker whose job mainly deals with shady "business oversights." With a meager salary, the only lodging they can afford is a shared room on one of the IPC's enterprise ships.

SkillList.Name: Clock In
SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Physical DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: Performance Boost
SkillList.SkillDesc: Receives 1 Performance Point after unleashing an attack. Performance Points can be seized by the attacker when this unit's Weakness is Broken or this unit receives a killing blow.

803301001.Name: Senior Staff: Team Leader
803301001.Introduction: An Interastral Peace Corporation senior staff member with a minimal rank of project team leader. The mech they drive belongs to the IPC. If damaged, its repair fees have to be paid out-of-pocket. With a half-decent salary, they can at least afford to rent a one-bedroom apartment on one of the IPC's enterprise ships.

SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals minor Physical DMG to a single target.

SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to a single target.

SkillList.Name: In Training...
SkillList.SkillDesc: Enters the Charge state. Uses Work Culture Shock in the next action.

SkillList.SkillDesc: Deals Physical DMG to all targets.

SkillList.Name: <unbreak>720</unbreak>-Degree Review
